    Demo Task 08 - Final complaint review (Closed / Review)
    ====================================================================

    Synthetic seed record for the case-management POC scoped application.
    This file is the EIGHTH and FINAL of the 8-task demo dataset; together
    with tasks 01 through 07, it satisfies the AAP requirement (Section
    0.7.4) of providing demo tasks that exercise the resolve-blocker and
    resolve-success gates on both case-type flows. The complete 8-task
    fixture matrix:

        Task 01 - Open        / Investigation / parent case 03 (In Progress GI)
        Task 02 - Closed      / Investigation / parent case 03 (In Progress GI)
        Task 03 - Open        / Follow-up     / parent case 04 (Pending GI)
        Task 04 - Closed      / Investigation / parent case 05 (Resolved GI)
        Task 05 - Closed      / Review        / parent case 05 (Resolved GI)
        Task 06 - In Progress / Investigation / parent case 08 (In Progress Complaint)
        Task 07 - Open        / Other         / parent case 08 (In Progress Complaint)
        Task 08 - Closed      / Review        / parent case 09 (Resolved Complaint)  ## THIS FILE

    The 8-task dataset thus exercises:
      * All 4 task types (Investigation, Review, Follow-up, Other) - this
        task contributes the second of two Review-type tasks (the other is
        task 05); the Review type semantically represents an agent's
        review action prior to resolving a case.
      * All 3 task statuses (Open, In Progress, Closed) - this task
        contributes the FOURTH of the four Closed tasks (the others are
        tasks 02, 04, and 05); the Closed status is the only status that
        the validate_resolved_transition subflow tolerates without
        blocking the case's Resolved transition.
      * 5 unique parent cases (03, 04, 05, 08, 09) - this task is the
        SOLE child of case 09; while case 05 has TWO Closed child tasks
        (04 + 05) demonstrating the multi-task resolve-success path on
        the General Inquiry flow, this task alone demonstrates the
        SINGLE-TASK resolve-success path on the Complaint flow.
      * Both flow paths (General Inquiry and Complaint) - this task tests
        the COMPLAINT flow's resolve-success path; tasks 04 and 05
        together test the GENERAL INQUIRY flow's resolve-success path;
        tasks 01 and 02 test the GENERAL INQUIRY flow's resolve-blocker
        path; tasks 06 and 07 test the COMPLAINT flow's resolve-blocker
        path.
      * Both resolve outcomes (BLOCKED via at least one non-Closed task,
        and SUCCESS via zero non-Closed tasks) - this task contributes
        to the SUCCESS outcome on the Complaint flow side.

    Lifecycle position - WHY Closed / Review / parent Complaint case
    Resolved is meaningful:
      Per AAP Section 0.5.5 the resolve gate's GlideRecord query
      executed inside the validate_resolved_transition subflow is:

          var gr = new GlideRecord('x_casemgmt_case_task');
          gr.addQuery('case', current.sys_id);
          gr.addQuery('status', '!=', 'Closed');
          gr.query();
          if (gr.next()) {
              // BLOCK: surface the verbatim error message
              //   "All tasks must be closed before resolving this case."
          } else {
              // ALLOW: zero non-Closed tasks - case may be Resolved
          }

      Case 09 is in Resolved status. With this single Closed child task,
      the query "case = case 09 AND status != Closed" returns ZERO rows.
      The subflow allows the In Progress -> Resolved transition.

      The Review task type captures the agent's final review action
      before signing off and submitting to the manager for closure. Per
      the AAP's Complaint case-handling pattern, the agent's last action
      before resolving is a comprehensive review of all gathered
      evidence and prior tasks. The "Final complaint review" subject
      makes this lifecycle phase explicit.

      The -2 days due_date is appropriate for a recently-due-then-
      completed task: due 2 days ago, marked Closed within the last 2
      days, and now case 09 has been Resolved. This contrasts with task
      05 (-3 days due, also Closed) where the Final review was completed
      slightly earlier in the General Inquiry flow's lifecycle. The
      relative date pattern uses negative offsets (yesterday/last week)
      to keep the demo data plausible regardless of when the Update Set
      is imported.

