        - The ACL records under ../../acl/ for case_task (table-level
             read/write/create/delete ACLs gate access for the demo
             agent and demo manager; the demo viewer reads via the
             read-all ACL)
        - ../users/sys_user_x_casemgmt_demo_agent.xml  (referenced by
             <assigned_to>; resolved by user_name lookup)
        - ../cases/x_casemgmt_case_demo_09.xml  (referenced by <case>;
             resolved by number lookup; this is the parent Resolved
             Complaint case whose resolve-success path this single
             Closed task exercises)

      This task IS REFERENCED BY (loaded AFTER this record):
        - The validate_resolved_transition subflow at
            ../../flows/sub_flows/validate_resolved_transition.xml
            FILTERS THIS TASK OUT of its non-Closed query. Because this
            task's status is Closed, the subflow's GlideRecord query
            for non-Closed child tasks of case 09 returns zero rows,
            allowing the In Progress -> Resolved transition. THIS TASK
            IS THE CANONICAL ENABLER OF THE COMPLAINT-FLOW RESOLVE-
            SUCCESS PATH FOR CASE 09. Where tasks 04 + 05 perform this
            role for case 05 on the General Inquiry flow, this task
            performs it ALONE for case 09 on the Complaint flow.
        - Dashboard report ../../reports/x_casemgmt_my_overdue_tasks.xml
            EXCLUDES this task from its "My Overdue Tasks" list; the
            list filter is "due_date < Today AND status != Closed AND
            assigned_to = current user", and this task's status=Closed
            disqualifies it. This is the correct behavior for a
            completed task.
        - The Agent Workspace dashboard's "Case count by status" donut
            counts case 09 (this task's parent) in the Resolved slice,
            not this task; the donut is keyed off case.status, not
            case_task.status.
        - The validate_closed_transition subflow checks at case-level
            (manager role, set closed_date), not task-level; this task
            does not directly participate in that subflow's logic.

